<h1>Markdown to HTML Converter Demo</h1>
<p>This is a <strong>demonstration</strong> of the Markdown to HTML converter tool. It showcases various <em>Markdown features</em> that are supported.</p>
<h2>Headers</h2>
<h3>This is an H3 header</h3>
<h4>This is an H4 header</h4>
<h5>This is an H5 header</h5>
<h6>This is an H6 header</h6>
<h2>Text Formatting</h2>
<p><strong>Bold text</strong> and <strong>also bold</strong> text examples.</p>
<p><em>Italic text</em> and <em>also italic</em> text examples.</p>
<p>You can also combine <strong><em>bold and italic</em></strong> formatting.</p>
<h2>Lists</h2>
<h3>Unordered List</h3>
<ul>
<li>First item</li>
<li>Second item</li>
<li>Third item</li>
<li>Nested item (manual indentation)</li>
<li>Another nested item</li>
</ul>
<h3>Ordered List</h3>
<ol>
<li>First numbered item</li>
<li>Second numbered item</li>
<li>Third numbered item</li>
</ol>
<h2>Links and Code</h2>
<p>Here's a link to <a href="https://www.google.com">Google</a> and an auto-link: <a href="https://github.com">https://github.com</a></p>
<p>Inline code example: <code>console.log("Hello, World!");</code></p>
<h3>Code Block</h3>
<pre><code>function greet(name) {
    return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}

const message = greet("World");
console.log(message);</code></pre>
<pre><code>def fibonacci(n):
    if n &lt;= 1:
        return n
    return fibonacci(n-1) + fibonacci(n-2)

print(fibonacci(10))</code></pre>
<h2>Blockquotes</h2>
<blockquote>
<p>This is a blockquote. It can contain multiple lines</p>
<p>and will be formatted appropriately in the HTML output.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>Another blockquote example.</p>
</blockquote>
<h2>Horizontal Rules</h2>
<p>Here's a horizontal rule:</p>
<hr>
<p>And another one:</p>
<hr>
<h2>Special Characters</h2>
<p>The converter handles special HTML characters like &lt;, &gt;, &amp; properly in regular text.</p>
<h2>Conclusion</h2>
<p>This demonstrates the core Markdown features supported by the converter tool. The generated HTML will be clean, well-formatted, and include proper CSS styling for a professional appearance.</p>
